1
00:00:49,184 --> 00:00:52,768
=In Love With Loving You=
(Based on Love by Erxi on Qimao)

2
00:00:52,768 --> 00:00:55,520
=Episode 10=

3
00:01:01,039 --> 00:01:01,679
Xuan.

4
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:04,959
Wu Shu told me everything.

5
00:01:05,239 --> 00:01:08,599
The reason you joined Song Group
and your situation there.

6
00:01:09,599 --> 00:01:10,480
Take this.

7
00:01:10,519 --> 00:01:11,760
Put it on your desk.

8
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:12,840
Within half an hour,

9
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,799
everyone in the company will know
you have a knight in shining armor.

10
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:17,079
Seriously?

11
00:01:17,079 --> 00:01:19,879
It's a passive skill
for Song Group employees, gossiping.

12
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,280
Here, let me hold it for you.

13
00:01:21,359 --> 00:01:22,079
Thanks.

14
00:01:32,719 --> 00:01:33,319
Mr. Song.

15
00:01:36,599 --> 00:01:38,560
See you later, Xuan.

16
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:43,559
Mr. Wu.

17
00:01:44,448 --> 00:01:45,599
Come to my office.

18
00:01:46,959 --> 00:01:47,560
Ji Xuan.

19
00:01:48,239 --> 00:01:50,760
This elevator's too crowded.
You should wait for the next one.

20
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:04,400
You and Ji Xuan...

21
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:06,519
Are you two dating?

22
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,439
Yes. My cousin is Ji Xuan's best friend.

23
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:11,680
I had the inside track.

24
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:14,319
Do you know

25
00:02:14,639 --> 00:02:16,680
the company forbids office romances?

26
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,039
Mr. Song.

27
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:23,479
I don't recall that being
in the company rules.

28
00:02:23,479 --> 00:02:26,000
Mr. Wu, you've been
working here for so long.

29
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:29,560
We have many written rules

30
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:31,360
and plenty of unwritten ones too.

31
00:02:32,159 --> 00:02:33,319
Ask Qiu Lin.

32
00:02:35,599 --> 00:02:36,879
Help me, help me.

33
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:42,639
Mr. Song.

34
00:02:43,439 --> 00:02:45,719
The company really
doesn't have that rule.

35
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,120
I remembered wrong?

36
00:02:53,039 --> 00:02:55,168
The person in charge
of the Xisha Resort is on leave.

37
00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:57,080
We need someone to step in.

38
00:02:58,960 --> 00:03:02,159
You mean to send me there?

39
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:05,039
Good pay, less work,
double the performance bonus.

40
00:03:05,039 --> 00:03:06,439
Maxed-out travel budget.

41
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:09,000
I'll go. I'll go.

42
00:03:10,159 --> 00:03:11,120
Goodbye, Mr. Wu.

43
00:03:12,439 --> 00:03:13,439
Goodbye, Mr. Song.

44
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,800
Are you and Wu Rui very close?

45
00:03:18,199 --> 00:03:20,479
No, we're just colleagues.

46
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:24,400
Mr. Song, everyone in the group knows

47
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,319
that Miss Xie is your fiancée.

48
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:29,080
If you say you are
banning office romances,

49
00:03:29,199 --> 00:03:30,759
that justification is too flimsy.

50
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:32,960
It won't reflect well on you.

51
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:36,240
Oh, so you were just being thoughtful.

52
00:03:36,759 --> 00:03:38,360
I thought you two had a deep friendship.

53
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,039
(I must not let him find out)

54
00:03:41,199 --> 00:03:43,840
(we were both once members
of the boss complaint group.)

55
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,680
Anyone there?

56
00:04:36,759 --> 00:04:37,680
Anyone there?

57
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,800
Can anyone hear me?

58
00:04:52,128 --> 00:04:54,400
(Wu Rui)

59
00:04:56,680 --> 00:05:00,319
Sorry, the person you're calling
is currently unavailable.

60
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:01,879
Why isn't he answering?

61
00:05:05,152 --> 00:05:07,488
(Mr. Qiu)

62
00:05:27,639 --> 00:05:28,279
Xuan.

63
00:05:29,399 --> 00:05:30,079
Mr. Song?

64
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:32,600
Miss Ji.

65
00:05:33,439 --> 00:05:36,360
Mr. Qiu ran a red light while driving
and got pulled over by the police,

66
00:05:37,079 --> 00:05:37,959
so I came.

67
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:44,480
Hello?

68
00:05:46,399 --> 00:05:48,360
Turn all the lights in the company on.

69
00:05:56,399 --> 00:05:58,879
We have a rule. No overtime after 9 PM.

70
00:05:59,279 --> 00:06:00,920
The power automatically cuts off.

71
00:06:01,199 --> 00:06:03,040
It's my fault that he ran the red light.

72
00:06:03,199 --> 00:06:04,560
I should still send him a message.

73
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,680
- No need.
- It's all...

74
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:08,759
I still should send one.

75
00:06:43,879 --> 00:06:44,920
It's no big deal.

76
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:47,720
Mr. Qiu and Wu Rui
are good friends privately.

77
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:51,720
I called Wu Rui, but he didn't answer,
so I contacted Mr. Qiu.

78
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,560
Wu Rui is on a business trip.
Didn't he tell you?

79
00:06:58,519 --> 00:06:59,279
He did.

80
00:06:59,879 --> 00:07:02,439
I... I was busy
looking up info on Mr. Yu.

81
00:07:02,639 --> 00:07:03,519
I forgot.

82
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:06,279
Alright.

83
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:07,959
Let me drive you home.

84
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,920
I can go back myself.

85
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:10,560
Let me.

86
00:07:20,079 --> 00:07:21,160
I'll go in.

87
00:07:21,279 --> 00:07:22,199
Thank you, Mr. Song.

88
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:23,800
Go to sleep early.

89
00:07:24,439 --> 00:07:25,040
Bye.

90
00:07:31,519 --> 00:07:32,160
Bye.

91
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:32,839
Good night.

92
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:50,480
Good night.

93
00:08:01,399 --> 00:08:02,000
(Ji Xuan.)

94
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:05,240
(When will I be able
to step into this yard legitimately?)

95
00:08:23,839 --> 00:08:24,800
Delivery guy.

96
00:08:25,399 --> 00:08:26,279
No insulated box.

97
00:08:59,399 --> 00:09:00,039
Mr. Song!

98
00:09:11,799 --> 00:09:13,320
Mr. Song, are you okay?

99
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,000
I'm fine.

100
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,519
I'll change your lock tomorrow.

101
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:21,360
To be safe, stay at my place tonight.

102
00:09:22,679 --> 00:09:23,264
Okay.

103
00:09:30,679 --> 00:09:32,720
You take the master bedroom.
I take the guest room.

104
00:09:33,279 --> 00:09:34,600
No need, Mr. Song.

105
00:09:34,639 --> 00:09:35,720
I sleep in the guest room.

106
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,000
It's fine.

107
00:09:37,399 --> 00:09:39,399
If you stay here,
word will get out eventually.

108
00:09:39,639 --> 00:09:42,159
Staying in the master bedroom
sounds much better.

109
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,200
You haven't eaten?

110
00:09:54,159 --> 00:09:56,639
These seem to be dishes
from my hometown.

111
00:09:58,039 --> 00:09:59,519
I'm more capable than you think.

112
00:10:03,904 --> 00:10:04,480
Try it.

113
00:10:09,919 --> 00:10:10,559
It's good.

114
00:10:11,759 --> 00:10:15,559
If you ever get tired of being CEO,
maybe consider becoming a food blogger.

115
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,919
But I only want to cook for you.

116
00:10:20,399 --> 00:10:21,159
Too cheesy.

117
00:10:27,879 --> 00:10:29,000
I'll be your blotting paper.

118
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:30,600
Let me do it.

119
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,799
You like roses too?

120
00:10:38,960 --> 00:10:39,600
Yes.

121
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:52,399
Do you have enemies?

122
00:10:54,279 --> 00:10:56,080
No enemies, just creditors.

123
00:10:56,399 --> 00:10:58,840
Have you ever dealt
with something like this before?

124
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:02,519
I've had paint thrown at me,
locks glued shut.

125
00:11:18,804 --> 00:11:20,596
♪In the vast sea of stars♪

126
00:11:20,756 --> 00:11:22,636
♪Flickering neon lights♪

127
00:11:22,836 --> 00:11:26,164
♪Longing spreads
throughout the universe♪

128
00:11:26,676 --> 00:11:28,948
♪Every star is♪

129
00:11:29,236 --> 00:11:33,108
♪My heartbeat for you♪

130
00:11:34,420 --> 00:11:36,244
♪Want to ride the evening breeze♪

131
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:37,956
♪And land in your arms♪

132
00:11:38,356 --> 00:11:41,812
♪The starry sky is like your eyes♪

133
00:11:42,068 --> 00:11:44,628
♪In the blue sky♪

134
00:11:44,692 --> 00:11:48,820
♪Your smile still lingers♪

135
00:11:49,748 --> 00:11:53,396
♪You are the brightest light
in my regrets♪

136
00:11:53,652 --> 00:11:57,316
♪You are the painful greeting
in my despair♪

137
00:11:57,524 --> 00:12:00,256
♪Can't find a cure♪

138
00:12:00,436 --> 00:12:04,948
♪To love you after we've parted♪

139
00:12:05,140 --> 00:12:09,172
♪You are the time I most want to keep♪

140
00:12:09,172 --> 00:12:12,768
♪The future I strive toward
in the darkness♪

141
00:12:12,896 --> 00:12:14,836
♪Slowly getting closer to you♪

142
00:12:14,932 --> 00:12:20,084
♪How I wish
I could give you my sunshine♪

143
00:12:20,724 --> 00:12:24,436
♪You are the brightest light
in my regrets♪

144
00:12:24,628 --> 00:12:27,380
♪Can't find a cure♪

145
00:12:27,508 --> 00:12:32,148
♪To love you after we've parted♪

146
00:12:32,316 --> 00:12:36,084
♪You are the time I most want to keep♪

147
00:12:36,308 --> 00:12:39,892
♪The future I strive toward
in the darkness♪

148
00:12:40,116 --> 00:12:42,016
♪Slowly getting closer to you♪

149
00:12:42,048 --> 00:12:47,156
♪How I wish
I could give you my sunshine♪
